# ============================================================
# WPO Pricing CLI
#
# For plain DOCX / born-digital PDF processing (or any run with --no-ocr),
# NO env vars are needed at all. Real OCR (a scanned PDF/image, without
# --no-ocr) needs exactly MISTRAL_API_KEY — read directly from process.env
# and injected straight into extractTextFromPdf() (@/lib/ocr/mistral.ts's
# `mistralApiKey` option). This CLI never imports @/lib/env (the web app's
# full schema — NODE_ENV, R2_*, ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY,
# ...) for OCR, so none of those are ever required here.
#
# Copy this file to tools/pricing-cli/.env.staging.local and fill in real
# values ONLY if you need:
#   (a) real OCR on scanned PDFs/images (no --no-ocr), and/or
#   (b) --from-staging to read a pricing_versions/pricing_language_rates row
#       from the real staging database (read-only — this CLI never writes).
#
# NEVER COMMIT REAL VALUES. *.local files are gitignored.
# ============================================================

# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Needed for real OCR (scanned PDF/image, no --no-ocr) — the ONLY var OCR needs.
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
MISTRAL_API_KEY=REPLACE_ME

# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Needed for --from-staging (read-only pricing_versions/pricing_language_rates fetch)
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://xxxxx.supabase.co
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=REPLACE_ME
